BBC Music magazine (August 2014)

ISSN: 0966-7180 | 108 pages | PDF


BBC Music Magazine is a must for anyone with a passion for classical music. Classical music connoisseurs and new enthusiast alike will enjoy the fascinating features and reviews of over 120 new works in every issue, including sections on jazz and world music.

IN THE AUGUST ISSUE:

* Helen Wallace meets the brilliant violinist Tasmin Little ahead of her performance of Moeran's Violin Concerto at the BBC Proms; 

* James Naughtie talks to the famous flautist Sir James Galway;

* Rick Jones follows the trail of 15 composers who couldn't ignore their wanderlust; 

* Stephen Johnson looks at the role of music criticism through history;

* the life and music of Jean-Philippe Rameau, one of the great masters of French baroque opera;

* and the best recordings of &quot;Symphonie Fantastique&quot;, Berlioz's monumental work

